In Saturday’s edition of the Racing Express, as found in The Citizen, jockey Muzi Yeni looks back at last week’s Derby Day and also previews the day’s meeting at Turffontein. Yeni, writing in his weekly column, reflects back on how Wilgerbosdrift Triple Tiara winner Rain in Holland stole the show and also mentions Aragosta winning the WSB SA Derby. On a personal note, Yeni highlights his big day by winning the Grade 1 Wilgerbosdrift HF Oppenheimer Horse Chestnut Stakes on MK’s Pride. Racing on Saturday takes place at Turffontein and Yeni previews all 10 races on the card. Click here for the full edition of Saturday’s Racing Express.